annotation.TEXT: Heck, yeah. Pool of water here for no real reason.
To be continued...
Yes, headbutting a stunned goomba is totally a way you can Yoshi stomp it. Just make sure you're not still ascending as you make contact, or you'll kick it instead.
So, back in we go!
Up next is a level that I think has More Than One Way to do it...
Totally.
Well, I would've liked to have burned something, but my accuracy sucked there!
Well, there's the goal. However, I'm not quite done with this level yet!
Whoa, Mario and Yoshi just kind of instantly disappeared when they went down that pipe.
Heck, yeah. Doin' victory dive bombs.
KA-BOOO- Gulp!
Okay, sliding worked there.
Well, I guess Mechakoopa isn't flammable or inflammable.
Ahem... I said, "Doin' victory dive bombs"!
Which level mode is this? 1E, I think? How come Nintendo didn't make use of level modes 1E and 1F in any of the original levels?
Neapolitan Bonaparte? No, that's not right...
As the level name indicates, there's More Than One Way to go in this level.
Gulp!
Nothing too terribly important, though. Just some coins and a power up.
Yeah, it can also go left... or up or down... Hey, that's more than two directions! And that's not even counting fancy directions like going forwards or backwards through time!
What the? Well, that's odd. Apparently, jumping at just the right angle with Yoshi lets you pass through a custom coin without collecting it.
Hold on... I'm not seeing the squiggly pieces here (the S and Z blocks)! What, were they considered too weird?
Mmm... Disco... (*drools*)

I wonder why the flower was able to reach that upper ledge the third time, but not the first two times? More random numbers at work here? Or, maybe it's a subpixel thing that nathanisbored could explain...
Heck, yeah. Bouncin' a flower.
Ooh, now this Ice Paradise is cool-looking!
Yep, we can actually go left from the start!
Ooh, pink! Wait, where'd my cape go? Didn't I finish the last level while caped?
Wait a minute... These look like Tetris blocks! What is this, Tuper Tario Tros.?
Barf!
Tar trouble? This can't be good...
Oh, man. These colors are making me hungry.
Oh, man. More fartin'.
There's the goal, but there is more stuff behind it.
See this diagonal stretch of dirt going off into space? It's pointless gameplay-wise, but it looks neat.
Uh, huh.
And, I get yet another 40.
Oh, man! Gotta make that vanilla exciting!
Mmm... Chocolate clouds... (*drools*)
That would be a good place to get Yoshi back if you ever lose him.
Aw, but what if I wanted to put nothing but 85 Thwomps in a level?
Gulp!
...Wait for it...
Triple kill!
So, blue koopas now give Yoshi fireballs, pink koopas give him flight, and yellow koopas... still give Yoshi gas.
Heck, yeah. Slidin' on Spinies... Honestly, there are times when there isn't really much to talk about in the annotations.
Ah, fudge! I missed the goal tape entirely this time!
Wait, a blue koopa isn't giving me flight? What's going on here?
Okay, I've gotta stop pretending Yoshi is a football player or a Pok√©mon and stop trying to Tackle everything!
Ah, fudge! Be careful. If it looks like it's boiling, it's probably as deadly as lava!
Gulp!
And, once again, I'm not going to break the whole level by flying over it. It doesn't look like there's anything of interest up there anyway.
Ooh, lucky for me that this tar isn't flammable or inflammable!
I don't know why that one fart failed...
Alright, so this map's 22 levels are now entirely complete! Next time, we start learning about stuff that we're not supposed to do!
Ooh, yummy strawberry juice! And it's totally safe to swim in, unlike that boiling hot Diet Coke from the previous level.

I remember the first time I've seen this happen. It was long ago, when I used a Game Genie on my SNES SMW to alter Mario's jumping physics, and then I watched the title demo, only to see it inevitably fail. Then, I was stuck playing the title level with the special world music playing until I reset.
Ooh, even the 1-up symbol is a delicious color!
Ah, well, whatever. Time for some Delicious Vanilla! Mmm... Delicious Vanilla... (*drools*)
I wonder why a standard goal wasn't used here... Is there a problem between it and level mode 1E?
Also, why did the game wait until I moved before giving me the save prompt?
Oh, yeah. You can safely walk behind this mushroom platform here. No devilishly hidden holes to worry about!
Well, anyway, in this level, black patches like this slow you to a crawl and greatly reduce your jump height.
Now, I don't know why this is like this, but the sand clouds won't appear if you've stomped at least one enemy in your jump, even though you still hear the sand clouds' sound effect.
...Ugh! I want that Yoshi coin! ...I'll have to Yoshi jump for it.
Wow, even my Yoshi jump's height was reduced there!
Heck, yeah. Fartin' while hittin' coin blocks.
Heck, yeah. Sayin' "Heck, yeah" a lot for no real reason.
What does "Neapolitan" mean anyway? (*Goes and checks...*) Noun: A native or citizen of Naples. Adjective: Of or relating to Naples. Well, that's a big help.
Apparently munchers like living in tarry environments.
Also, don't include a plethora of precision jumps in a slippery level.
Also, blue berries now increase the timer, and the other berries... don't do anything special without greater quantities.
And, what does this have to do with hacking tips? Maybe it's just to demonstrate a custom block?
Oh, man! Secret exit! ...Wait... If this level has two exits, why isn't it colored red on the map?
Still no 50? I'll get a 50 sooner or later. I just know it. But, for now, it's bonus game time!
Yoshi can certainly use Lick and Stomp nicely, and depending on what he's eaten (and/or what color he is), he can also use Sand-Attack, Fly, or Flamethrower.
Oh, and that bubbling black stuff? That's really hot Diet Cola, which burns just as much as lava. (At least there's no Mentos around here!)
D'oh! Sliding with Yoshi can be hit or miss sometimes.
Heck, yeah. Perfectin' a bonus game.
Heck, yeah. Makin' an odd Yoshi noise.
Toast- Wah! Well, that was a toasty fail!
Gulp!

Hello, and welcome back to Hacks 101! Last time, I played the 17 levels that make up the top three rows of this map, but they were all pretty much single-screen things, so now let's get to work on this bottom row, which is made up of actual "level" levels.
Ooh, Yoshi coin! That one was sooo tricky to find!
